libsoundio
------------------------------------------
libsoundio is a lightweight abstraction over various sound drivers. It
provides a well-documented API that operates consistently regardless of the
sound driver it connects to. It performs no buffering or processing on your
behalf; instead exposing the raw power of the underlying backend.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libpulse0-17.0-4
  libsoundio-devel-2.0.0-1bl2
  libsoundio2-2.0.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libpulse-devel-17.0-4
  ninja-1.13.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/andrewrk/libsoundio

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/andrewrk/libsoundio/archive/refs/tags/2.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsoundio-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsoundio-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsoundio-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsoundio-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsoundio2-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsoundio-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsoundio)
  /usr/bin/sio_list_devices.exe
  /usr/bin/sio_microphone.exe
  /usr/bin/sio_record.exe
  /usr/bin/sio_sine.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsoundio.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsoundio/CHANGELOG.md
  /usr/share/doc/libsoundio/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libsoundio/README.md

(libsoundio2)
  /usr/bin/cygsoundio-2.dll

(libsoundio-devel)
  /usr/include/soundio/endian.h
  /usr/include/soundio/soundio.h
  /usr/lib/libsoundio.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsoundio.pc

